[30;1m49 | [0m[35m    """A key-value store for Fragments. Used to implement the @st.fragment decorator.[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m51 | [0m[35m    We intentionally define this as its own protocol despite how generic it appears to[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35m    be at first glance. The reason why is that, in any case where fragments aren't just[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m    stored as Python closures in memory, storing and retrieving Fragments will generally[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m    involve serializing and deserializing function bytecode, which is a tricky aspect[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m    to implementing FragmentStorages that won't generally appear with our other *Storage[0m

[30;1m2065 | [0m[35m        # Every node up to the end is a Block[0m
